💡 Concept

Build a full Active Directory-based IAM system that simulates a real company:

Departments (HR, IT, Finance, etc.)
Role-based access
Automated provisioning
Lifecycle management (Joiner–Mover–Leaver)

This is exactly what many internal IAM teams still run.

🧱 What You’ll Implement
🏢 1. Active Directory Domain Design
Create domain (e.g., corp.local)
Organizational Units (OUs):
Users
Computers
Departments (HR, IT, Finance)
Group structure:
Role groups (e.g., HR_Read, IT_Admin)
Security groups for access control
👤 2. Automated User Provisioning (PowerShell)
Script to:
Create users from CSV
Assign department
Add to correct groups
Set home directories
🔄 3. Lifecycle Management
Joiner: Auto-create + assign access
Mover: Change department → update permissions
Leaver:
Disable account
Remove group memberships
Archive home directory
🔐 4. RBAC (Role-Based Access Control)
Map:
Roles → Groups → Permissions
Apply NTFS permissions on shared folders
📁 5. File Server Access Control
Shared folders:
\\corp\HR
\\corp\Finance
Restrict access using AD groups
📊 6. Auditing & Logging
Enable:
Logon auditing
Object access auditing
Script to pull security logs
